#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:1
msgid "An attribute for deprecation"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:3
msgid ""
"![Minimum Rust version: 1.9](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.9-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:5
msgid ""
"If you're writing a library, and you'd like to deprecate something, you can "
"use the `deprecated` attribute:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:10
msgid "\"0.2.1\""
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:11
msgid "\"Please use the bar function instead\""
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:14
msgid "// ...\n"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:18
msgid ""
"This will give your users a warning if they use the deprecated functionality:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:20
msgid ""
"```text\n"
"   Compiling playground v0.0.1 (file:///playground)\n"
"warning: use of deprecated item 'foo': Please use the bar function instead\n"
"  --> src/main.rs:10:5\n"
"   |\n"
"10 |     foo();\n"
"   |     ^^^\n"
"   |\n"
"   = note: #[warn(deprecated)] on by default\n"
"\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:32
msgid "Both `since` and `note` are optional."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-2018/the-compiler/an-attribute-for-deprecation.md:34
msgid ""
"`since` can be in the future; you can put whatever you'd like, and what's "
"put in there isn't checked."
msgstr ""
